Django Messages Framework Styling (Priority: HIGH)

Implementation: Add to base.html

Requirements:
    Display success messages (green alert)
    Display error messages (red alert)
    Display info messages (blue alert)
    Auto-dismiss after 5 seconds (JavaScript)
    Positioned at top of content area (not blocking navigation)

Example Code (Bootstrap 5):

xml
{% if messages %}
<div class="messages-container">
  {% for message in messages %}
    <div class="alert alert-{{ message.tags }} alert-dismissible fade show" role="alert">
      {{ message }}
      <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="alert"></button>
    </div>
  {% endfor %}
</div>
{% endif %}

Testing:
    Create a new case
    Verify success message appears: "Fall '[alias]' erfolgreich erstellt"
    Try invalid form submission
    Verify error message appears
    Check messages auto-dismiss after 5 seconds

Acceptance Criteria:
    Messages display correctly styled
    Auto-dismiss works
    Multiple messages stack correctly
    Messages don't block content

